  "text": "The API call chain for Grafana to Loki instant queries operates as follows:\n\n1. **Grafana HTTP Client Type**: In grafana/grafana at pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go, the LokiAPI struct (lines 29-34) acts as the HTTP client wrapper for Loki queries. It wraps a standard net/http.Client with URL, logger, and tracer fields.\n\n2. **Grafana Query Execution Flow**: When Grafana receives a query request, the Service.QueryData method (pkg/tsdb/loki/loki.go:182) processes it. This calls the LokiAPI.DataQuery method (pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go:161), which:\n   - Uses makeDataRequest (pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go:46) to build the HTTP request to /loki/api/v1/query\n   - Sets query parameters: query (LogQL expression), time (Unix nanoseconds), direction, and limit\n   - Executes the request via api.client.Do(req) where api.client is the underlying http.Client\n\n3. **Loki Request Parsing**: On the Loki side, the incoming HTTP request to /loki/api/v1/query is handled by ParseInstantQuery function (pkg/loghttp/query.go). This function:\n   - Receives the raw *http.Request\n   - Extracts query parameters using helper functions: query(r), limit(r), ts(r), direction(r), shards(r)\n   - Returns an InstantQuery structure containing the parsed parameters\n\n4. **Loki Query Execution**: The parsed request is then routed to InstantQueryHandler (pkg/querier/http.go), a method on the QuerierAPI struct, which:\n   - Receives the converted LokiInstantRequest\n   - Validates the syntax (ensures it's a sample expression, not a log selector)\n   - Executes the query against the Loki query engine\n   - Returns the result as a logqlmodel.Result\n\nThe complete call chain: Grafana Service.QueryData → LokiAPI.DataQuery → HTTP request to Loki /loki/api/v1/query → Loki ParseInstantQuery → InstantQueryHandler → query execution and response."
}

